Somali Refugees in Ethiopia British psychiatrist Dr Lynne Jones returns to the Somali refugee camp in Ethiopia for a close up view of the trauma caused by the years of violence in Somalia. Dr Jones has set up a scheme to help people with mental health problems. Ladies' Special The BBC's Geeta Pandey talks to commuters aboard Delhi's first women only train. Sara Wheeler The travel writer tells Audrey Brown about her latest adventures in the Arctic Circle and why she took her baby with her. He new book is called "The Magnetic North". Show less